  "title": "Video by selfcarelivingdays",
  "description": "I used to think paying for Japanese food is super not worth it until @ganko.sushi_sg \n\nIt is one of the BEST Japanese restaurants in Singapore I’ve been to 🍣❤️✨\n\nThey apparently have their ingredients airflown from Japan 3x a week, so it’s super fresh and of high quality 🤤 \n\nIt’s not cheap, but you get what you pay for and I think it’s a great place to splurge on for special occasions ❤️\n\nMy favourites were:\n🐟Truffle Sashimi Don 8.8/10 - super fresh fish and filled with premium ingredients like freshly shaved truffle, uni and caviar 🤩 incredibly luxurious \n\n🍣 Premium Nigiri Platter 8.6/10: super fresh, sweet & clean tasting sashimi slices!!! It’s the first time I feel knife skills matter 😜 really very smooth, buttery tuna slices 👍🏻\n\n🥪 Wagyu Sando 8.2/10: Wagyu leaner cut but still has that rich, buttery fragrance - good if you’re not into that creamy fatty taste that typical Wagyu has ✨\n\nOverall, a great place for dates and special occasions ❤️\n\n📍Ganko Sushi\n9 Penang Rd, 01-01, Singapore 238459\n\n#sg #sgfoodies #japanesefood #sashimi #sushi",
